      "content": "That's a common concern, but unfortunately, it's not that simple. The body metabolizes medications unevenly across the day, and topical interactions like these can happen regardless of the time gap between consumption. Even a short time gap may not be enough to neutralize the grapefruit's inhibitory effect on the atorvastatin. It's still best to consult your doctor or pharmacist for personalized guidance to ensure your safety.",
